Question 3
(a) System calls:
1.open()
2.read()
3.write()
4.close()

(b) 1.write() – Write data to the source file.
2.read() – Reading data from the source file.

(c) C system call sequence:
START
src ← open("source.txt", READ)
dest ← open("dest.txt", CREATE/WRITE)
WHILE read(src, buffer) > 0
    write(dest, buffer)
END WHILE
close(src)
close(dest)
STOP

Question 4
(a) 1.fork() – Creates a new child process.
2.exec() – Replaces the child process with a new program.

(b) wait() makes the parent process wait until the child process finishes.

(c) C system call sequence:
START
pid ← fork()
IF pid = 0 THEN
    exec("program")
ELSE
    wait()
END IF
STOP

